{
  "title": "Benchmarking Cron-Driven Tasks Using FastAPI in Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This guide explains how to benchmark cron-driven tasks using FastAPI, a modern, fast (high-performance), web framework for building APIs with Python 3.12+.",
  "key_points": [
    "FastAPI is optimized for high performance and easy-to-use.",
    "Cron jobs are automated tasks that run at specific times or intervals on Unix-like operating systems.",
    "Benchmarking helps to understand the task's performance and identify areas for optimization.",
    "Combining FastAPI with cron jobs enables efficient, scalable, and maintainable benchmarking of periodic tasks."
  ],
  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "```\n\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI\nimport time\n\napp = FastAPI()\n\ndef cron_task():\n    start_time = time.time()\n    # Your task code here\n    end_time = time.time()\n    elapsed_time = end_time - start_time\n    return elapsed_time\n\n@app.get('/cron-task')\ndef benchmark():\n    result = cron_task()\n    return {'elapsed_time': result}\n```"
    }
  ],
  "version_notes": [
    "This example uses Python 3.12+ and FastAPI version 0.73.0.",
    "Make sure to install the required packages by running `pip install fastapi uvicorn aiofiles`."
  ],
  "caveats": [
    "Ensure your cron job executes the FastAPI script, and it's correctly configured to run as a web server (e.g., with Gunicorn or Uvicorn).",
    "Adjust the `cron_task()` function to include your actual task, and replace `# Your task code here` with the appropriate code.",
    "This example uses basic timing for benchmarking. For more accurate measurements, consider using profiling libraries like cProfile or line_profiler."
  ]
}
